h Primitives for Long-Term...\"/>\n  <script src=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/js/cite.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script><meta name=\"citation_title\" content=\"RPPNet: Perceptually-Grouped Rhythm-Pitch Primitives for Long-Term Structure Melody Generation via Boundary-Aware Modeling\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Zhang, Tieyao\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Liu, Yuke\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Yu, Jiaxing\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Wu, Xinda\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Zhang, Kejun\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Chen, Genfang\" /><meta name=\"citation_date\" content=\"2026/07/22\" /><meta name=\"citation_online_date\" content=\"2026/07/22\" /><meta name=\"citation_pdf_url\" content=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2607.19776\" /><meta name=\"citation_arxiv_id\" content=\"2607.19776\" /><meta name=\"citation_abstract\" content=\"Existing symbolic music generation models typically use bars as the basic structural unit. However, human perception of musical phrases often does not align with notated bar lines, leading to long-term structural fragmentation. This paper proposes RPPNet-a two-stage deep learning architecture with variable structural boundaries. It first generates variable-length Rhythm-Pitch Primitive (RPP) sequences, where each RPP encodes note count, rhythm, and contour; then decodes the RPP sequences into concrete notes. The grouping of RPPs is automatically derived from acoustic cues, auditory inertia, and similarity perception based on music psychology. Experiments show that melodies generated by RPPNet are superior in both long-term structure and musicality, with significant improvements across all subjective evaluation dimensions. Ablation studies confirm that the performance gain stems from the structural correctness of the psychological representation, rather than from model capacity. This work offers an interdisciplinary perspective for music generation, integrating music theory, computational modeling, and music psychology.\" />\n        placeholder=\"Search papers by title, author, abstract, or ID...\">\n        dc:title=\"RPPNet: Perceptually-Grouped Rhythm-Pitch Primitives for Long-Term Structure Melody Generation via Boundary-Aware Modeling\"\n    <h1 class=\"title mathjax\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Title:</span>RPPNet: Perceptually-Grouped Rhythm-Pitch Primitives for Long-Term Structure Melody Generation via Boundary-Aware Modeling</h1>\n    <div class=\"authors\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Authors:</span><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Zhang,+T\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tieyao Zhang</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Liu,+Y\" rel=\"nofollow\">Yuke Liu</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Yu,+J\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jiaxing Yu</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Wu,+X\" rel=\"nofollow\">Xinda Wu</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Zhang,+K\" rel=\"nofollow\">Kejun Zhang</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Chen,+G\" rel=\"nofollow\">Genfang Chen</a></div>            <div id=\"download-button-info\" hidden>View a PDF of the paper titled RPPNet: Perceptually-Grouped Rhythm-Pitch Primitives for Long-Term Structure Melody Generation via Boundary-Aware Modeling, by Tieyao Zhang and 5 other authors</div>\n    <blockquote class=\"abstract mathjax\">\n            <span class=\"descriptor\">Abstract:</span>Existing symbolic music generation models typically use bars as the basic structural unit. However, human perception of musical phrases often does not align with notated bar lines, leading to long-term structural fragmentation. This paper proposes RPPNet-a two-stage deep learning architecture with variable structural boundaries. It first generates variable-length Rhythm-Pitch Primitive (RPP) sequences, where each RPP encodes note count, rhythm, and contour; then decodes the RPP sequences into concrete notes. The grouping of RPPs is automatically derived from acoustic cues, auditory inertia, and similarity perception based on music psychology. Experiments show that melodies generated by RPPNet are superior in both long-term structure and musicality, with significant improvements across all subjective evaluation dimensions. Ablation studies confirm that the performance gain stems from the structural correctness of the psychological representation, rather than from model capacity. This work offers an interdisciplinary perspective for music generation, integrating music theory, computational modeling, and music psychology.\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Subjects:</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell subjects\">\n            <span class=\"primary-subject\">Sound (cs.SD)</span>; Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI)</td>\nView a PDF of the paper titled RPPNet: Perceptually-Grouped Rhythm-Pitch Primitives for Long-Term Structure Melody Generation via Boundary-Aware Modeling, by Tieyao Zhang and 5 other authors</div><li><a href=\"/pdf/2607.19776v1\" aria-describedby=\"download-button-info\" accesskey=\"f\" class=\"abs-button download-pdf\">View PDF</a></li><li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/html/2607.19776v1\" class=\"abs-button\" id=\"latexml-download-link\">HTML (experimental)</a></li><li><a href=\"/src/2607.19776v1\" class=\"abs-button download-eprint\">TeX Source\n      <div class=\"abs-license\"><a href=\"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/\" title=\"Rights to this article\">view license</a></div>\n         accesskey=\"p\" title=\"previous in cs.SD (accesskey p)\" rel=\"nofollow\">&lt;&nbsp;prev</a>\n         title=\"next in cs.SD (accesskey n)\"  rel=\"nofollow\">next&nbsp;&gt;</a>", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
